      "id": "step-1-overview",
      "title": "Project Overview",
      "description": "ZeroLeaks is an autonomous AI security scanner that tests LLM systems for prompt injection vulnerabilities. It uses a multi-agent architecture with Tree of Attacks (TAP) to systematically explore attack vectors and identify weaknesses in system prompt defenses. The codebase is organized into three main pillars: agents (the brain), probes (the arsenal), and knowledge (the research base).",
